  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump operates in an in vivo surgical environment where extended perfusion runs of 6–12 hours are routine; roller pump occlusion wear, motor bearing degradation, and transient flow sensor drift are documented failure modes in clinical practice. All model simulations and validation experiments were conducted under nominal hardware assumptions with factory-new components and steady boundary conditions; no fault injection, degraded-actuator, or sensor-error scenarios were introduced into the computational or experimental campaign.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-req-001",
